# Liahona.AI Continuity

## Continuity Philosophy

Continuity should preserve meaningful evolution through time.

The goal is not endless accumulation.

The goal is semantic preservation.

## Preserve

Preserve:
- architectural decisions
- governance shifts
- deployment checkpoints
- behavioral breakthroughs
- source-structure evolution
- meaningful implementation transitions
- operational lessons
- continuity summaries

## Avoid Preserving

Avoid preserving:
- repetitive logs
- raw conversational noise
- tiny implementation tweaks
- redundant iterations
- low-signal debugging history

## Checkpoint Structure

Continuity checkpoints should summarize:
- what changed
- why it changed
- what problem it solved
- what layer it affected
- next architectural frontier

## Layer Awareness

Continuity should distinguish:
- Canonical
- Interpretive
- Runtime
- Projection
- Continuity

Do not flatten all changes into a single undifferentiated history.

## Compression

As the project grows:
- summarize
- consolidate
- compress semantically
- preserve signal over noise

Continuity should remain:
- readable
- meaningful
- restrained
- navigable